title.narrative: Management Support and Technical Assistance Services

description.narrative: The purpose of this contract is to assist the USAID Africa Bureaus Office of Sustainable Development (AFR/SD) to achieve its strategic goals. Specifically the project: 1) Supports USAID economic growth and trade related activities in sub-Saharan Africa (SSA), including AFR/SDs role serving as the Secretariat for the USAID Trade Hub Management Counci; 2) Provides logistical and administrative support for the planning, knowledge management, communications, and outreach for all technical divisions of AFR/SD; and 3) Provides technical services to AFR/SD and all its technical divisions in formulating a new, robust, cross-cutting and inclusive strategy in content areas including but not limited to health; education; conflict; peacebuilding; governance; economic growth; agriculture and trade via a multi-sectoral approach to achieving development goals, deepening understanding of development trends, and improving program performance while integrating gender and environmental considerations and requirements.
